#week-title("Three", "Opening the Year One Letter")

=== Core Teaching

At the close of Year One, the student sealed a letter to their future self —
an honest account of where they stood at the end of twelve months of study.
That letter is now opened.

Reading it is a specific kind of alchemical act: it is the return of the
volatile to the fixed from a distance of a full year. The person who sealed
that letter and the person who opens it are not identical. Two years of genuine
practice — of meditation, laboratory work, inner Nigredo, long circulations,
metal meditations — have changed the practitioner in ways that are sometimes
visible and sometimes not.

*What to attend to in the reading:*
- What did you predict about Year Two that came true?
- What surprised you most about what the year actually held?
- What intentions did you carry that were genuinely fulfilled?
- What did you not know at the end of Year One that you now know clearly?
- What did you know at the end of Year One that two years of practice have
  complicated, deepened, or revised?

The letter is not a historical document only. It is a diagnostic instrument:
the gap between what the Year One self expected and what the present Initiate
has actually experienced is itself a map of what the Work has done and is
doing.

After reading and reflecting, the student writes a reply — a paragraph from
the present self to the Year One self. This reply acknowledges what the Year
One self understood correctly, what it could not have known, and what the
present self would want it to know. This reply is not sealed — it is kept open
in the journal as a continuous dialogue.

The student then writes a new letter to be sealed and opened at the close of
Year Three.

=== Topics This Week

- Reading the Year One sealed letter
- The diagnostic value of the gap between intention and experience
- Writing the reply to the Year One self
- Sealing a new letter to be opened at the end of Year Three

#inner-work[
  *The Open and the Sealed*

  The sealed letter and its opening enact a central alchemical movement: the
  volatile enclosed, matured, and then released. What was sealed as a
  potential has had two years to develop under the heat of practice. What is
  now released is neither the original intention nor a disappointment of it —
  it is something that could only have come from the time between sealing and
  opening.

  Write both the reply to Year One self and the new sealed letter before
  the end of this week. The sealed letter is for Year Three Month 12.
]

